critique: This document pertains to land withdrawal for reclamation purposes, specifically modifying previous executive orders to enable the Secretary of the Interior to withdraw public land in California for reclamation under the act of June 17, 1902. Given the subject matter, the document has minimal ideological content. It does not directly address immigration, executive power, federalism, national security, economic regulation, or social inclusion. Therefore, most axes should be scored as neutral. The action of modifying an existing executive order could be seen as a very slight expansion of executive power, but it is primarily an administrative action related to land management.
